results.name: How many more primes than irreducible GF(2)[X] polynomials there are in range [2^n,2^(n+1)].
link: A. Karttunen, Scheme-program for computing this sequence.
Index entries for sequences operating on GF(2)[X]-polynomials
example: There are 5 primes (17,19,23,29,31) in range [16,32], while there are only 3 irreducible GF(2)[X]-polynomials in the same range: (19,25,31), thus a(4)=2.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Jan 03 2004
